description: Data corresponding to body sensor's worn by first responders. This can include vitals readings and location information.
name: First responder body sensor data

description: Data collected from the public. This could be data extracted from social media or data explicitly sent to public safety entities. For example, video and images texted directly to a PSAP.
name: publicly sourced data

description: Data whose value correspond to their real time availability and integrity.
name: situational awareness data

description: A data type for a single or set of related actions, events, or process steps.
name: Activity Type

description: A data type for a device.
name: Device Type

description: A data type for a human being.
name: Person Type

description: A data type for a conveyance designed to carry an operator, passengers and/or cargo, over land.
name: Vehicle Type

description: Information gathered about a patient that is intended to be passed along to another healthcare entity. For example, information that may be loaded into a hospital's patient management system.
name: Healthcare Information

description: Information having an implicit or explicit association with a location relative to the Earth. This data can be incorporated and used by Geographic Information Systems (GIS)
name: Geographic Data

resource_links.description: Standard representation of geographic point location by coordinates

resource_links.desdes: The Interagency Modeling and Atmospheric Assessment Center coordinates and disseminates Federal atmospheric dispersion modeling and hazard prediction products. These products provide the Federal position during actual or potential incidents involving hazardous material releases
resource_links.hyperlink_name: Interagency Modeling and Atmospheric Assessment Center
